{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"109b4c26-4445-45f1-8d57-e652296a0840","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"DisplayName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1d9ba971-5c90-4cd7-a35c-3f50e7ed36d0","outputTokens":166},"id":"893616ba-c961-45df-a308-52a79e11960c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:49:09.348Z","parentId":"c6a781ee-3993-41a3-beef-ad75626c2338"}
